          <hr>
          <div class="headingdiv">
          <span><h1>What to Do if you lose a pet.</h1></span>
        </div>
        <hr>
          <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              Contact all the animal welfare organisations (see list below). Don’t just
              contact those in your area – sometimes people pick up an animal in one area
              and then drop them off at an organisation far away. Check-in regularly with the
              animal organisations and even visit regularly if you can.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              Contact all the local vets in your area.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Put up posters – street corners, local shops, schools, etc.
               Also go and knock on every single door in your surrounding neighbourhood.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              Contact your local neighbourhood watch/ security company
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              Advertise on facebook – each animal welfare organisation has its own page.
              However, the following pages are also helpful: Missing Pets SA,
              Petfinders, Lost and Found, Traffic fines, cameras & updates in Cape Town,
               Barking Mad, Western Cape Animals, Pets Reunited
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p> Advertise on the following websites:</p>
              <ul>
                <li><a href="http://www.gumtree.co.za/s-lost-found/v1c9032p1"> Gumtree Lost and Found</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://petfinders.co.za/"> Petfinders</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://www.capetown.gov.za/en/CityPetFinder/Pages/default.aspx">City Pet Finder</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://www.petslostandfound.co.za/">Pets Lost and Found</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://lostdogs.co.za/"> Lost Dogs</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.parrotalert.com/"> Parrot Alert</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://www.pets.org.za/"> PETS</a></li>
              </ul>
          </li><br>


          <li>
            <p>
              Advertise in the newspapers: Cape Times, Argus, Weekend Argus, Tygerburger, local community papers eg Tatler
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
             <a href="http://petfinders.co.za/">Pet Finders</a> is a highly recomended website and they are based in Cape Town.
             <a href="www.missingpetpartnership.org">Missing Pet Partnership</a>,although American-based,also has some useful information.
            <a href="https://plus.google.com/b/111561530458523055661/">Pet Finders</a>, follow them and get intouch with them on GooglePlus.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              Put up posters – street corners, local shops, schools, etc.
               Also go and knock on every single door in your surrounding neighbourhood.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              Those with missing STAFFIES, PITBULLS ETC, please report your pet as possibly stolen to the police and insist on a case number (Numbers and statistics
              are needed to enforce the need for task forces to combat dogfighting rings). Also, report your missing animals
              here:<a href="http://satruth.co.za/main/">Satruth</a>
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <p>
              <b>Pet Whisperers/Pet Detectives:</b>
              <ul>
        <li>Animal Trax: Carol – Tel: 021 939 7045 / 083 457 5652, email: carol@animaltrax.co.za</li>
        <li>Paws and Listen: Naomi Pretorius – Tel: 028-3164561, email: pawsandlisten@vodamail.co.za</li>
        <li>Send details plus a photo to info@animalspirit.co.za for a referral to an animal communicator</li>
      </ul>
            </p>
          </li>


          <li>
            <h5><b>PLEASE BEWARE OF SCAMMERS!:</b></h5>
              <p>
              eg. A lady named Ayanda from MAA Animal Continent Mitchells plain claiming to have a team of
              people that will find your missing pet. Obviously for a fee! and they need your ID Number. No such organisation exists!
            </p>
          </li>
